i had this issue before working with an old HD, so i switched to SSD and reinstalled everything including windows and still have this issue

#### What is the expected behavior?
Table should render new rows when the dataSource changes, whilst also making intelligent updates with trackBy function.

#### What is the current behavior?
The table initially renders correctly, but if the dataSource changes and a new item's been added, the table doesn't render a new row for it, if also making use of the when predicate.

#### What are the steps to reproduce?
```
<table mat-table [dataSource]="dataSource" multiTemplateDataRows [trackBy]="trackBy">
...
    <tr [class.expanded]="expandedEntity == row" class="grouped-row-header"
            *matRowDef="let row; columns: ['group']; when: shouldRenderTypeRow" mat-row></tr>
    <tr *matRowDef="let row; columns: columnsToDisplay; when: shouldRenderDocumentationRow" mat-row></tr>
    <tr [class.is-last-of-same-group]="isLastRowOfSameGroup(i)" class="grouped-row-body"
            [hidden]="shouldHideDocumentationRow(row)"
            *matRowDef="let row; columns: columnsToDisplay; when: shouldRenderNestedDocumentationRow;"
            mat-row></tr>
</table>
```


